<li id="cite_note-48"><b><a href="#cite_ref-48" title="">^</a></b> Searle, John. (1980). "Minds, Brains and Programs", <i>Behavioral and Brain Sciences</i>, vol.3. (<a href="http://www.bbsonline.org/Preprints/OldArchive/bbs.searle2.html" class="external text" title="http://www.bbsonline.org/Preprints/OldArchive/bbs.searle2.html" rel="nofollow">online</a>)</li>
<li id="cite_note-49"><b><a href="#cite_ref-49" title="">^</a></b> Block, Ned. (1980b). "Troubles With Functionalism", in Block (1980a).</li>
<li id="cite_note-50"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50" title="">^</a></b> Fodor, J. and Lepore, E. <i>Holism: A Shopper's Guide</i>. Blackwell. Oxford. 1992.</li>
<li id="cite_note-51"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51" title="">^</a></b> Dummett, Michael. <i>The Logical Basis of Metaphysics</i>. Harvard University Press. Cambridge (MA). 1978.</li>
<li id="cite_note-52"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52" title="">^</a></b> Penco, Carlo. <i>Olismo e Molecularismo</i> in <i>Olismo</i> ed. Massimo Dell'Utri. Quodlibet. Macerata. 2002.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Stein-53"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Stein_53-0" title="">^</a></b> Steinitz, Y. (1994), “Brains in a Vat: Different Perspectives”, Philosophical Quarterly 44.</li>
<li id="cite_note-54"><b><a href="#cite_ref-54" title="">^</a></b> Brueckner, A. (1986), “Brains in a Vat”, Journal of Philosophy 83.</li>
</ol>
